docs.lead_paragraph: It’s still early in literary awards season — the winners of the Man Booker Prize, the Nobel Prize for Literature and the National Book Awards won’t be announced until later this fall — but speculation started heating up this week about who will take home the world’s most prestigious literary prizes this year.

docs.abstract: Mayor Bill de Blasio pledged to bring more openness to how police officers are disciplined, but, unable to get action in Albany, he has largely disappeared on the issue.
docs.snippet: Mayor Bill de Blasio pledged to bring more openness to how police officers are disciplined, but, unable to get action in Albany, he has largely disappeared on the issue.
docs.lead_paragraph: This past week Mayor Bill de Blasio conducted two excursions in downtown Manhattan, one of them to visit his junior-year dorm room at New York University and another to walk the High Line, a park he had famously ignored, with a group of third-graders. It was a good thing they didn’t come at him with a barrage of questions about congestion pricing and why it would take 10 years to close Rikers Island, because Mr. de Blasio did not appear to be in the mood for inquiry.

headline.main: What Happened to Police Accountability? The Mayor’s Not Saying
headline.print_headline: De Blasio Falters On Police Reform

docs.abstract: The six candidates seem to believe the surest way to win votes is not to vow to lock people up, but to offer policies to keep them out of jail.
docs.snippet: The six candidates seem to believe the surest way to win votes is not to vow to lock people up, but to offer policies to keep them out of jail.
docs.lead_paragraph: It is a sign of the times — and perhaps of a place — that for several months now the six lawyers running for Brooklyn district attorney have rarely mentioned what has, at least historically, been the central issue in law-enforcement races: fighting crime.

headline.main: In Brooklyn’s District Attorney Race, the Focus Isn’t on Prosecuting Crime
headline.print_headline: In a Race to Become Brooklyn’s District Attorney, Fighting Crime Rarely Comes Up

docs.abstract: Mayor Lyda Krewson promised to curb violence and heal racial divisions. Then a former police officer was acquitted of murder.
docs.snippet: Mayor Lyda Krewson promised to curb violence and heal racial divisions. Then a former police officer was acquitted of murder.
docs.lead_paragraph: ST. LOUIS — After hours of mostly peaceful protests over a white former police officer’s acquittal in the fatal shooting of a black man, a crowd of demonstrators gathered in St. Louis Friday night outside the new mayor’s house. Soon, rocks were flying.

headline.main: Amid Protests, St. Louis Mayor Walks a Political Tightrope

docs.abstract: Despite a show of sideline support, a group consisting largely of white billionaires has reluctantly addressed social injustice and head injuries.
docs.snippet: Despite a show of sideline support, a group consisting largely of white billionaires has reluctantly addressed social injustice and head injuries.
docs.lead_paragraph: The image was striking — several owners of N.F.L. teams locking arms with their players on the sidelines Sunday in a dramatic statement of defiance to a president who ridiculed their sport and condemned players for refusing to stand during the national anthem as a protest against racism.

headline.main: N.F.L. Owners’ Unity With Players Might Be Short-Lived
headline.print_headline: Owners Clutch Their Players  But Protect the N.F.L. Shield

docs.abstract: The Civilian Complaint Review Board found that Officer Daniel Pantaleo used a chokehold and restricted Eric Garner’s breathing, a person familiar with the case said.
docs.snippet: The Civilian Complaint Review Board found that Officer Daniel Pantaleo used a chokehold and restricted Eric Garner’s breathing, a person familiar with the case said.
docs.lead_paragraph: A New York City agency that investigates police misconduct has found that the officer who put his arm around the neck of  Eric Garner before his death did use a chokehold and restricted Mr. Garner’s breathing, a person familiar with the case said on Friday.

headline.main: Review Board Recommends Stiffest Punishment for Officer in Garner Case
headline.print_headline: Review Board Finds Officer Used Chokehold on Garner
